      • getArguments

        private static String getArguments(Executable method,
                                   boolean typed)
        Returns the argument list of the given method. Method supports 2 modes
        • typed mode : arguments are following their types
        • untyped mode : arguments are printed without any types
        Parameters:
        method - Executable that can be either Method or Constructor - method to generate arguments list of
        typed - indicates whether a mode should be typed or not
        Returns:
        String containing text of arguments list of the given method that consists of
        • list of method's argument names separated by ", " for untyped mode
        • list of method's argument types fully-qualified names followed by method's argument names separated by ", " for untyped mode

      • getMethodImpl

        private static String getMethodImpl(Executable method,
                                    String newClassName)
        Generates default implementation source code of the given method assuming that it is a method or a constructor of a class with name = newClassName. Implementation is generated to be correct implementation of the given method and formated using Oracle's java code style
        Parameters:
        method - method or constructor to generate implementation of
        newClassName - name of class containing the given method
        Returns:
        method's default implementation. If the given method is a method then the body of it consists of a single return-statement. Return value is the default value of method's return type. If method's return type is void then return statement has no return value If the given method is a constructor then the body of it consists of a single super constructor invocation statement. Current method's arguments are delegated to super

      • implement

        public void implement(Class<?> token,
                      Path root)
               throws ImplerException
        Description copied from interface: Impler
        Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

        Generated class full name should be same as full name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List should go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java

        Specified by:
        implement in interface Impler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        root - root directory.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.
